<item>
            <title>[LDAP-177] LdapUtils convertLdapException fails to convert exceptions when they are extended</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/LDAP-177</link>
                <project id="10071" key="LDAP">Spring LDAP</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Changes to LdapUtils were made to facilitate &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/LDAP-100&quot; title=&quot;LdapUtils#convertLdapException fails to convert some NamingExceptions to the narrowest possible type&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LDAP-100&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LDAP-100&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. However, by changing the checks to be based on the class, versus doing an instanceof comparison, sub-classes of the exceptions do not meet the condition and are all being classified as UncategorizedLdapException.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, the &lt;tt&gt;javax.naming.NameNotFoundException&lt;/tt&gt; is defined by Apache DS as &lt;tt&gt;LdapNameNotFoundException extends javax.naming.NameNotFoundException&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="26197">LDAP-177</key>
            <summary>LdapUtils convertLdapException fails to convert exceptions when they are extended</summary>
